00:00:26.840 --> 00:00:29.280
First Thessalonians chapter five this evening,

00:00:29.280 --> 00:00:31.360
First Thessalonians chapter number five.

00:00:31.360 --> 00:00:35.580
We started in verse number 12 about three months ago now.

00:00:35.580 --> 00:00:39.240
And we've been studying through these instructions

00:00:39.240 --> 00:00:42.479
that God gives to the church there in Thessalonica.

00:00:42.479 --> 00:00:44.880
And he begins with, we beseech you.

00:00:44.880 --> 00:00:47.400
And then of course he transitions in verse 14.

00:00:47.400 --> 00:00:50.319
We exhort you and we find that as we've read through

00:00:50.319 --> 00:00:54.479
and studied these particular instructions,

00:00:54.479 --> 00:00:57.439
that we would say that the closing section of this book

00:00:57.439 --> 00:01:00.560
is packed with powerful truth.

00:01:00.560 --> 00:01:04.000
And I would call it profitable instruction.

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:06.919
We understand that God's word is profitable.

00:01:06.919 --> 00:01:09.480
We understand that the second Timothy chapter three

00:01:09.480 --> 00:01:11.959
in verse number 16 tells us that all scripture

00:01:11.959 --> 00:01:14.800
is given by inspiration of God and is profitable.

00:01:14.800 --> 00:01:16.720
It tells us what it's profitable for,

00:01:16.720 --> 00:01:18.680
but this is profitable instruction.

00:01:18.680 --> 00:01:21.680
And we find that every New Testament church

00:01:21.680 --> 00:01:25.919
should have a desire to walk worthy and please God.

00:01:25.919 --> 00:01:28.599
That of course has been the title for this series

00:01:28.599 --> 00:01:30.000
over the last 13 weeks.

00:01:30.000 --> 00:01:33.400
And this evening as we examine two verses of scripture,

00:01:33.400 --> 00:01:36.599
we've been spending, really in verse 14,

00:01:36.599 --> 00:01:38.879
we spent several weeks looking at each phrase.

00:01:38.879 --> 00:01:40.660
And then over the next several weeks,

00:01:40.660 --> 00:01:43.199
we've kind of just dealt with one verse per week.

00:01:43.199 --> 00:01:46.040
But this evening, verse number 20 and 21

00:01:46.040 --> 00:01:50.580
really tie together and establish a single truth

00:01:50.580 --> 00:01:52.779
that needs to be understood.

00:01:52.779 --> 00:01:56.699
And really, I believe that the scriptures are clear

00:01:56.699 --> 00:02:00.360
that we are to be sound in the faith.

00:02:00.360 --> 00:02:04.699
We find that God has desire for his children

00:02:04.699 --> 00:02:08.500
and for his churches to be sound in the faith.

00:02:08.500 --> 00:02:11.479
That word sound means to be healthy.

00:02:11.479 --> 00:02:14.779
It means to be free from any mixture of error.

00:02:14.779 --> 00:02:18.820
You will find the phrase there in the book of Titus

00:02:18.820 --> 00:02:20.619
of being sound in the faith.

00:02:20.619 --> 00:02:22.300
You'll find in the book of Titus

00:02:22.300 --> 00:02:24.220
and the book of 1 Timothy

00:02:24.220 --> 00:02:26.399
and a number of other books as well,

00:02:26.399 --> 00:02:29.660
where they'll use the word sound doctrine

00:02:29.660 --> 00:02:34.339
and that which is free of any error, mixture of error.

00:02:34.339 --> 00:02:37.139
And so we find that God desires for his people,

00:02:37.139 --> 00:02:39.720
his churches to be sound in the faith.

00:02:39.720 --> 00:02:42.059
As you read the pastoral epistles,

00:02:42.059 --> 00:02:43.979
as you read the letters that are given

00:02:43.979 --> 00:02:45.380
to the New Testament churches,

00:02:45.380 --> 00:02:48.699
such as this one to the church at Thessalonica,

00:02:48.699 --> 00:02:52.059
you will know that there is an emphasis placed

00:02:52.059 --> 00:02:56.539
on the importance of being settled, grounded,

00:02:56.539 --> 00:02:58.860
and established in the faith.

00:02:58.860 --> 00:03:00.979
And that's what God wants for his people.

00:03:00.979 --> 00:03:03.380
He doesn't want us to be tossed to and fro.

00:03:03.380 --> 00:03:06.139
He doesn't want every time some new thing comes up

00:03:06.139 --> 00:03:08.460
for us to be swaying back and forth

00:03:08.460 --> 00:03:09.779
and we're over here and we're over there

00:03:09.779 --> 00:03:10.660
and we don't know what.

00:03:10.660 --> 00:03:14.179
No, he wants us to be settled and grounded

00:03:14.179 --> 00:03:17.339
and to have that solid foundation.

00:03:17.339 --> 00:03:20.539
And so God provided us with his word

00:03:20.539 --> 00:03:23.860
and we believe the Bible is the sole authority

00:03:23.860 --> 00:03:26.979
for faith and for practice.

00:03:26.979 --> 00:03:31.539
And so I'm thankful that God has given us his word.

00:03:31.539 --> 00:03:34.220
We understand that the church in Thessalonica

00:03:34.220 --> 00:03:36.300
and many of the churches, as we look at the churches

00:03:36.300 --> 00:03:38.779
that are written to here in the New Testament,

00:03:38.779 --> 00:03:41.339
they did not have the entire Bible

00:03:41.339 --> 00:03:43.059
like we have this evening.

00:03:43.059 --> 00:03:44.940
And so we understand that God,

00:03:44.940 --> 00:03:47.619
during that foundational period of time

00:03:47.619 --> 00:03:50.860
that we often refer to as the early church age,

00:03:50.860 --> 00:03:54.179
in the first century, that God had established

00:03:54.179 --> 00:03:57.339
that there would be some apostolic sign gifts,

00:03:57.339 --> 00:03:59.660
that there would be some truth

00:03:59.660 --> 00:04:01.899
with regard to some spiritual gifts

00:04:01.899 --> 00:04:05.059
that would be for that era of time.

00:04:05.059 --> 00:04:06.779
And we see really that here,

00:04:06.779 --> 00:04:09.100
as we look at this portion of scripture,

00:04:09.100 --> 00:04:11.339
that he's dealing with part of that,

00:04:11.339 --> 00:04:14.139
but we find that it's been preserved for us this evening

00:04:14.139 --> 00:04:16.220
and it's applicable for every church

00:04:16.220 --> 00:04:18.100
throughout the church age.

00:04:18.100 --> 00:04:21.940
We have the whole Bible and we ought to be thankful for that

00:04:21.940 --> 00:04:24.179
and here in these two verses of scripture,

00:04:24.179 --> 00:04:27.380
I believe that God provides his people

00:04:27.380 --> 00:04:30.540
with a simple formula that will enable

00:04:30.540 --> 00:04:33.619
individual believers and churches

00:04:33.619 --> 00:04:36.700
to be sound in the faith.

00:04:36.700 --> 00:04:38.619
Notice what he says in verse number 20,

00:04:38.619 --> 00:04:42.540
despise not prophesying, verse 21,

00:04:42.579 --> 00:04:47.579
prove all things, hold fast that which is good.

00:04:48.820 --> 00:04:51.779
Really, those three statements are going to serve

00:04:51.779 --> 00:04:54.260
as our three points for an outline this evening.

00:04:54.260 --> 00:04:56.579
And so number one, verse number 20,

00:04:56.579 --> 00:04:58.700
despise not prophesying,

00:04:58.700 --> 00:05:00.100
as I've titled the message this evening,

00:05:00.100 --> 00:05:01.739
sound in the faith.

00:05:01.739 --> 00:05:04.299
How can we be sound in the faith?

00:05:04.299 --> 00:05:07.260
How could this church, the church in Thessalonica,

00:05:07.260 --> 00:05:08.619
how could they be sound in the faith?

00:05:08.619 --> 00:05:11.339
How could any church be sound in the faith?

00:05:11.339 --> 00:05:14.140
Maybe we can ask this question as well this evening.

00:05:14.140 --> 00:05:18.540
Are there churches that are not sound in the faith?

00:05:18.540 --> 00:05:21.739
Obviously, the answer is obvious to that question.

00:05:21.739 --> 00:05:24.739
There are an abundance of churches

00:05:24.739 --> 00:05:26.540
that are not sound in the faith.

00:05:26.540 --> 00:05:29.779
How can we make that statement this evening?

00:05:29.779 --> 00:05:32.859
Well, because what they teach and what they practice

00:05:32.859 --> 00:05:37.700
doesn't align with the book that God gave us, the Bible.

00:05:37.700 --> 00:05:41.140
And I'm so thankful for that little song that we sing,

00:05:41.940 --> 00:05:44.100
so often with the children in Sunday school, the B-I-B-L-E.

00:05:44.100 --> 00:05:46.700
Yes, that's the book for me.

00:05:46.700 --> 00:05:50.459
I stand alone on the word of God, the B-I-B-L-E.

00:05:50.459 --> 00:05:53.980
