00:06:10.279 --> 00:06:14.040
these prophesying that Paul is referring to

00:06:14.040 --> 00:06:16.839
when he says despise not prophesying?

00:06:16.839 --> 00:06:19.320
Well, we have to understand this evening

00:06:19.320 --> 00:06:21.559
the ministry of prophets.

00:06:21.559 --> 00:06:22.959
What is the ministry of prophets?

00:06:22.959 --> 00:06:26.600
Well, prior to the New Testament being completed,

00:06:26.600 --> 00:06:29.000
we find that prophets would speak

00:06:29.000 --> 00:06:32.140
direct revelation from God.

00:06:32.140 --> 00:06:34.920
Now that the Bible is completed,

00:06:34.920 --> 00:06:38.000
we find that there are no longer prophets

00:06:38.000 --> 00:06:42.440
in the sense of speaking direct revelation from God.

00:06:42.440 --> 00:06:45.480
For the Bible, the canon of scripture is closed.

00:06:45.480 --> 00:06:48.600
Now we could look at a preacher and say,

00:06:48.600 --> 00:06:50.040
some might use that terminology,

00:06:50.040 --> 00:06:53.279
that they're forth telling, they're giving truth.

00:06:53.279 --> 00:06:56.799
But the reality is that that office of a prophet,

00:06:56.799 --> 00:07:00.119
when Paul was speaking here about despise not prophesying,

00:07:00.119 --> 00:07:03.920
we must understand what the New Testament teaches us

00:07:03.920 --> 00:07:06.500
about the ministry of prophets.

00:07:06.500 --> 00:07:09.140
Understand also this evening that prophets,

00:07:09.140 --> 00:07:10.980
apostles and prophets,

00:07:10.980 --> 00:07:14.339
