00:07:14.339 --> 00:07:17.619
We understand that Jesus Christ is the cornerstone.

00:07:17.619 --> 00:07:21.140
The prophets and the apostles are the foundation.

00:07:21.140 --> 00:07:23.179
And then we find that Peter refers to,

00:07:23.179 --> 00:07:24.980
we see in the book of Ephesians as well,

00:07:24.980 --> 00:07:26.700
that we are lively stones.

00:07:26.700 --> 00:07:29.980
We're like the bricks of the structure of the church,

00:07:29.980 --> 00:07:33.019
if we could think about it in that image this evening.

00:07:33.019 --> 00:07:35.500
And so look back, if you will, to the book of Ephesians,

00:07:35.500 --> 00:07:39.779
and notice what God tells us about prophets.

00:07:39.779 --> 00:07:43.459
And it helps us to understand what Paul is dealing with here

00:07:43.459 --> 00:07:45.140
in the church in Thessalonica,

00:07:45.140 --> 00:07:47.380
when he says despise not prophesying.

00:07:47.380 --> 00:07:49.160
